01/04/2011
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Parliament decided on Thursday (March 31st) to postpone its population census until October 1st.
The decision was made for financial reasons.
The two-week census was supposed to be conducted in April.
The last population census was carried out in 2002.
Meanwhile, population censuses kick off on Friday in Montenegro and Croatia.
The process in Montenegro will last until April 15th while in Croatia it will run through April 28th.
(Tanjug, Blic, Beta, RTS, RTCG, HRT - 31/03/11)
